        The doSum function description = it adds two numerics
        Parameters:
        a - the A parameter, can be NA
        b - the B parameter
        Returns:
        A+B of course, NAs in inputs are converted to null in Java. This catches the resulting NPE in java idiom and returns an explicit NA. This only matters if you care about the difference between NA_real_ and NaN in R.
